Reports for social media claim sey wen year finish, di Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN), go stop to give Form A, di tin wey dey help Nigerians wey dey outside kontri pay school fees. Nigerians wey dey abroad dey get dollars through di ‘Form A’ for official price rather dan for black market wey dey always cost pass. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-719182" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM.jpeg" alt="" width="1080" height="682" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM.jpeg 1080w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM-300x189.jpeg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM-1024x647.jpeg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM-768x485.jpeg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM-24x15.jpeg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM-36x23.jpeg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/WhatsApp-Image-2022-06-29-at-7.38.30-AM-48x30.jpeg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px" /> Di tori don dey worry plenti Nigerians for social media sake of say from January 2023, dia outside kontri school fees go add, according to di news. Adewale Adetona tok for Twitter say, “I just read say from December 2022, CBN dey cancel Form A. Nigerians wey wan go school outside kontri go need buy dollars from black market.  Evrytin just dey wowo.” Di post get 179 retweets, 22 quote tweets, and 368 likes. I just read that from December 2022, the CBN is canceling Form A. Prospective International Students from Nigeria will have to get FX for their school fees from black market. It keeps getting worse. — Adewale Adetona (@iSlimfit) June 21, 2022  Di claim also comot for Twitter and Facebook wit one picture wey dem tok say na from Manchester Metropolitan University. Di title wey follow di post tok say, “Central Bank don stop to give discount for di Form A moni from 31st December 2022”. Apparently Manchester Metropolitan University sent this circular alleging that CBN is withdrawing form A by end of 2022 for fee payments. Japa via studies about to be more expensive if true. pic.twitter.com/FOPPz0PpkY — AW (@DipoAW) June 21, 2022  <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-718082" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Facebook-Form-A.jpg" alt="" width="522" height="597" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Facebook-Form-A.jpg 522w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Facebook-Form-A-262x300.jpg 262w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Facebook-Form-A-21x24.jpg 21w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Facebook-Form-A-31x36.jpg 31w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Facebook-Form-A-42x48.jpg 42w" sizes="(max-width: 522px) 100vw, 522px" /> Manchester Metropolitan University don ansa TheCable follow di management of Manchester Metropolitan University tok, to confam weda na dem tok di claim. “We understand sey CBN wan put back di moni wey dem bin reduce before from di Form A, na why we come help our students so dat dem no go enta wahala,” na so di spokesperson tok. Wetin we check Osita Nwanisobi, director of di corporate communications department for CBN, sey the advise wey Manchester Metropolitan University give dia students no get head. Nwanisobi sey, “CBN no tok dat kyn tin.” He advise parents and students sey make dem no folo any talk wey say make dem pay dia school sharp sharp through Flywire before December 31, 2022. Final tok CBN neva make any official statement wey sey dem go stop to dey provide Form A. Di claim no true. 